newsitem.title: USA: FOB Gulf Grain - Markets quiet, mostly steady.
newsitem.headline: FOB Gulf Grain - Markets quiet, mostly steady.

text.p: FOB Gulf basis values for winter wheat were unchanged, while slight changes were noted in corn and soybean values, dealers said.
The wheat, corn and soybean markets were quiet with a lack of export business to attract material to the U.S. Gulf.
Taiwan is scheduled to tender overnight for 54,000 tonnes of U.S. No.2 corn for December 10-25 shipment from the U.S. Gulf or December 26-January 9 from the Pacific Northwest.
Dealers quoted the following afternoon FOB U.S. Gulf values, basis Chicago futures, except hard red winter wheat basis Kansas City. (In cents per bushel).
